ae_description: During an after school survey, the participant asked Nicole Fajardo, who was administering the survey, what incapacitated meant. She then followed by giving an example of what happened to her 'Like how my mother was drugged and used to beat (us/me?)'. She spoke about it in past tense.     The student didn't specify whether this happened with her biological mother back in her home country or in the U.S. with her adoptive mother.    We attempted to follow up with the student the same day at around 8 PM by calling but there was no response to clarify the timeline of the suspected abuse.     We called Family and Child Services to make a report and were told that there wasn't sufficient information to meet the guidelines to follow through the report.  They said that the information we have doesn't meet the criteria of child abuse and doesn't show that the child is in imminent danger.     Next morning at 9 AM we followed up with the Wellness Coordinator, Lizbett Calleros, who is aware of the students' significant abuse history in her home country and continues to work closely with her to support her in building coping skills and connecting her to resources. The Wellness Coordinator acknowledged that the student's statement is consistent with her abuse history outside of the U.S. She also shared that the student's adoptive mother is also closely engaged at the school level in the student's care.     Tatiana Baquero Devis (Sr CRC) went to the school during and with the help of Wellness Center pulled the student from class to clarify. Tatiana asked the student when the abuse she mentioned to Nicole had happened. The student said that it had taken place in Colombia with her biological mother, before the student moved to the United States. Tatiana asked the student if she feels safe at home and the student said yes, that she feels safe with her adoptive mother/family and had only referred to what had happened prior to coming to the U.S. to be with her adoptive family.

referral_notes: This is the student from my group who previously had not scored high during Pre-Program  Data Collection but who had a change in demeanor. Student has now scored high during Post-Program Data Collection. I already made a referral to Wellnes for this student. Wellness does not have the bandwidth to see him in-house and they don't have Spanish provider in-house. They are also wrapping up all school-based services since school is almost over.    I was able to talk to him on 5/4 about a referral to CAS. He said that he has done therapy in the past but does not want to do therapy at the moment and does not want to be connected to services. Wellness is aware of this and also let me know that he is frequently ditching class and got into a fight on 5/10. They are in touch with him and were also pleasantly surprised that he has shown up to Fuerte very consistently, even when he doesn't show up to classes that same day. He was only absent from Fuerte once out of 7 sessions.
